  with 2 malformed Javac tree cases
  with a throwable : java.lang.NullPointerException
```

Rename refactoring of `Element` in the code below leaves `foo` as is:

``` ceylon
interface I<T> {
    shared formal T foo(T t);
    shared formal T bar(T t);
}

class C<Element>() satisfies I<Element> {
    shared actual Element bar(Element t) => t;
    foo(Element t) => t;
}
```

Autocompleting the refinement of `visit()`, results in this code:

``` ceylon
object x extends Visitor() {
    shared actual void visit(Resource? resource) {}

}
```

Its should be `Tree.Resource`, not just plain `Resource`.

Given this class:

``` ceylon
object x extends Visitor() {
    shared actual void visit(Tree.Resource? resource) {}
    //here
}
```

Attempting to autocomplete refinements of additional overloads of `visit()` fails to show any options.

Find References and Find Assignments are broken w/r/t shortcut member refinement.

``` ceylon
interface Super {
    shared formal String name;
    shared void m() {
        printIt(name);
    }
}

class Sub1() satisfies Super {
    name = "Gavin";
}
class Sub2() satisfies Super {
    shared actual String name = "Bastien";
}
```
- Selecting `name` in `Super` and running either Find References or Find Assignments should give me the assignment in `Sub1`. 
- And in the case of Find References, it's also supposed to give me the refinement in `Sub2`, IIRC, though I'm not 100% sure on that one.

Given:

``` ceylon
    if (1==1 || 2==1) {

    }
    else {

    }
```

Try "invert if/else statement". It gives you:

``` ceylon
    if (!1==1 || 2==1) {

    }
    else {

    }
```

Which isn't correct, since `!` has a higher precedence than `||`. IMO, it should give you:

``` ceylon
    if (1!=1 && 2!=1) {

    }
    else {

    }
```

Given:

``` ceylon
shared class Run() {
    shared void method() {
        Date date = now().date();
        print(date);
    }
}
```

If I select the expression `now().date()` and invoke Extract Function, the new `function` declaration is placed inside `method()`. It should be placed _outside_ `method()`. This was due to a recent change to the typechecker, I suppose.

Enter the following class definition:

``` ceylon
class C() {
    shared String s = "";

}
```

In the blank line, type `equa`, Ctrl+Space, and auto-complete the `shared actual Boolean equals(Object that)` entry. The result is:

``` ceylon
class C() {
    shared String s = "";
    shared actual Boolean equals(Object that) {
        if (is C that) {
            return s==that.s && 
                ;
        }
        else {
            return false;
        }
    }
}
```

`&&;` is, of course, a syntax error.

This probably broke during the migration to Ceylon, but that’s just a guess.

<sub>Aside: this broken code also causes backend errors, though they don’t happen on the CLI. Should I report these in ceylon/ceylon?</sub>

